&lt;hr /&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16380091" author="githubbot" created="Wed, 28 Feb 2018 10:12:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user StephanEwen commented on a diff in the pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/5594#discussion_r171196255&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/5594#discussion_r171196255&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &amp;#8212; Diff: flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/runtime/rest/AbstractHandler.java &amp;#8212;&lt;br/&gt;
    @@ -84,8 +84,8 @@ protected AbstractHandler(&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;     	@Override&lt;br/&gt;
     	protected void respondAsLeader(ChannelHandlerContext ctx, Routed routed, T gateway) throws Exception {&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if (log.isDebugEnabled()) {&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;log.debug(&quot;Received request &quot; + routed.request().getUri() + &apos;.&apos;);&lt;br/&gt;
    +		if (log.isTraceEnabled()) {
	&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;End diff &amp;#8211;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;    Does `routed.request().getUri()` perform some decoding work? If not, why not simply use&lt;br/&gt;
    ```java&lt;br/&gt;
    log.trace(&quot;Received request {}.&quot;, routed.request().getUri());&lt;br/&gt;
    ```&lt;br/&gt;
    which should be very efficient (no object creation, string concatenation, etc). Results even in less byte code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
